\begin_layout Standard
Two test cases are developed to tune parameters and to validate the use
 of multi-fluid equations to represent dry, two-dimensional sub-grid-scale
 convection.
 The first is transient; the standard rising bubble of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "BF02"

\end_inset

 and the second is steady state with heat transfer at boundaries.
 For each we aim to reproduce the vertical heat transport, mean velocity
 of the rising air, bouyancy of the rising air and pressure differences
 between two fluids in a single column two fluid model.
 For both test cases the reference solution is a single fluid solution of
 the two-dimensional Boussinesq equations at high horizontal and vertical
 resolution.
 
\end_layout

